Conversations



Please select a filter and/or a date range




1 August 2017
‘The future is bright, but different’ – BP’s chief on half-year results and the broader business outlook
As BP releases its half-year financial results, group chief executive Bob Dudley shares his thoughts on business milestones so far in 2017, the importance of long-term planning for lower oil prices and why the world will continue to need all forms of energy in a lower carbon future


20 June 2017
'There is no other place in the world like it' - marking 40 years on Alaska's North Slope
When oil started pumping from Alaska's Prudhoe Bay field on 20 June 1977, estimates pointed to a 30-year production life span with potential for 9.6 billion barrels. In fact, Prudhoe Bay has proved to be the most productive US oil field to date, generating more than 12.5 billion barrels in four decades. To mark the production anniversary, meet two staff who have made their careers on the surprisingly flat, North Slope


10 May 2017
Future potential: how Mauritania and Senegal are set to become new players in natural gas supply
It’s not every day that a brand new global supply of energy is unlocked. But that is what BP, in partnership with Kosmos Energy, is striving to achieve with a project to bring newly discovered natural gas resources off the coast of Mauritania and Senegal onto the world market. As this new partnership begins, BP Magazine asks regional president Emma Delaney what is involved in setting up operations in a new country. 








Locations



Please select a filter and/or a date range




28 June 2017
The Incredible Hull: BP celebrates 50 years of operations at UK chemicals site
Technological breakthroughs, giant engineering projects and a visit from the Queen are just some of the highlights from BP’s site in Hull in the UK over the past half-century. BP Magazine looks back at its history and a new business which is paving the way for the future


8 June 2017
BP geared for success in Mexico
For the first time in 75 years, companies outside Mexico are allowed to invest in the country’s fuels market following deregulation by the Government. The move has seen BP become the first global brand to open a fuel station in the country, with plans for more than 1,000 to follow in the next five years


1 June 2017
The energy giant: why Russia matters
Prolific oil and gas resources, an experienced workforce, economical production costs and huge potential for growth: Russia has all the qualities to support BP’s strategic shift towards natural gas and highly competitive oil production. BP Magazine talks to BP Russia president David Campbell to find out more








