Analysis of BP Plc

March 2016
100 pages
Aruvian's R'search
        

Report ID: 3703411



Summary
Table of contents
Search Inside


		BP Plc, formerly known as British Petroleum, is one of the biggest oil and gas companies in the world. The company is known as one of the 'supermajor' oil and gas companies. The company, based out of London, UK, operates across all areas in the oil and gas industry. The company is also active in the petrochemical industry, power generation, trading, and also has interests in renewable energy such as wind power and biofuels.Aruvian Research presents Analysis of BP Plc. A complete and comprehensive analysis of BP Plc, includes an overview of the industry the company operates in, a PEST Framework Analysis of the industry, and then moves on to analyzing the company itself.Company analysis from Aruvian includes a history of BP Plc, a business segment analysis of the segments BP Plc operates through, a look at the organization structure of the company, a geographical operating segments analysis, an analysis of the company’s major competitors.A financial analysis of BP Plc is presented in the report which includes a ratio analysis, basic profit and loss analysis, presentation of the company balance sheet, and much more. A SWOT Framework Analysis of BP Plc and an analysis of three of its competitors completes this in-depth company analysis.
	

		A. Executive SummaryB. Looking at the IndustryB.1 Industry DefinitionB.2 Brief Profile of the IndustryB.3 Impacts on the IndustryB.4 Challenges Facing the IndustryB.5 Future PerspectiveC. Industry PEST Framework AnalysisC.1 Political Aspects C.2 Economic AspectsC.3 Social AspectsC.4 Technological AspectsD. Looking at BP PlcD.1 Company ProfileD.2 History of the CompanyD.3 Ownership Pattern in the CompanyD.4 Organizational DivisionsD.5 Profiling the Key ExecutivesD.6 Products & ServicesE. Looking at BusinessE.1 Business SegmentsE.2 Geographical SegmentsE.3 Company SubsidiariesF. BP Plc: SWOT Framework AnalysisF.1 Strengths to Build UponF.2 Weaknesses to OvercomeF.3 Opportunities to ExploitF.4 Threats to OvercomeG. Profiling the CompetitionG.1 Chevron CorporationG.1.1 Corporate ProfileG.1.2 Business Segment AnalysisG.1.3 Financial AnalysisG.1.4 SWOT AnalysisG.2 Exxon Mobil CorporationG.2.1 Corporate ProfileG.2.2 Business Segment AnalysisG.2.3 Financial AnalysisG.2.4 SWOT AnalysisG.3 Royal Dutch Shell PlcG.3.1 Corporate ProfileG.3.2 Business Segment AnalysisG.3.3 Financial AnalysisG.3.4 SWOT AnalysisH. BP Plc: Financial AnalysisH.1 Current FinancialsH.2 Balance SheetH.3 Profit & Loss StatementH.4 Ratio AnalysisI. BP Plc: Future PerspectiveJ. Glossary of Terms
	







